author: Tasha Hegarty
title: Ellie Goulding denies lip-syncing at AFL Grand Final: 'What a rad compliment' - Showbiz
text: Ellie Goulding has denied claims she was lip-syncing at the AFL Grand Final in Australia today (October 3).A sound glitch during her performance of 'Love Me Like You Do' was enough to convince Twitter that she wasn't singing live.Love it when people think I lip sync, what a rad compliment :) Now where does one find a good veggie restaurant in Melbs?â€” Ellie Goulding (@elliegoulding) October 3, 2015Goulding didn't seem too bothered about the claims, and was more interested in finding a veggie restaurant.The AFL Grand Final is a massive sporting event in Australia, on par with the FA Cup Final, Wimbledon or the Grand National. If you're interested, Hawthorn beat West Coast Eagles by 46 points.For those not in the know, Australian Football is very different to football as we know it in the UK, as kicking, handballing and running with the ball are all allowed.Goulding recently admitted she wants to get married and is just waiting for boyfriend Dougie Poynter to pop the question.Watch her music video for latest single 'On My Mind' below:
